 50% on the Nintendo Switch edition of Bluey: The Videogame, which drops the price from $40 down to $20. Released in 2023, Bluey: The Videogame has the same animation style of the TV show and has its own story that plays like an interactive episode in the series. It supports local multiplayer for up to four players--Bluey, Bingo, Bandit, and Chilli are the playable characters--and has a collection of minigames from episodes of the show.Before you buy it, you may want to check out the upcoming Amazon-exclusive edition of Bluey: The Videogame. Outright Games is releasing a bundle for Nintendo Switch that includes a pair of adorable Gnome plushies inspired by the characters who live in the Heeler family's garden. You can preorder Bluey: The Videogame Gnome Plush Bundle for $50 ahead of its October 17 release.There's no shortage of Bluey interactive toys and activities, but a handful of the most exciting additions to the sprawling Bluey toy catalog arrived in stores on June 1: Lego Bluey playsets. The launch lineup features three Lego sets recommended for kids ages four and up and two Duplo playsets for toddlers. Check them out below: Got a news tip or want to contact us directly? Email news@gamespot.com",
